{"task": "pytest-dev__pytest-8399", "arm": "atelier", "rep": 1, "ok": true, "cost_usd": 0.21590050000000002, "duration_ms": 72325, "duration_api_ms": 67745, "num_turns": 13, "input_tokens": 3097, "cache_read_tokens": 142901, "cache_creation_tokens": 7834, "output_tokens": 2025, "models": ["claude-opus-4-8"], "is_error": false, "result_excerpt": "Tests pass (59 passed, 9 skipped). Verified: fixture now hidden under plain `--fixtures`, shows only with `-v` as `_unittest_setUpClass_fixture_Tests`.", "valid": true, "validity_reason": "", "correct": true, "score": 1.0, "judge_model": "swebench", "judge_reason": "resolved", "saved_usd": 0.0, "saved_tokens": 0, "thinking_tokens": 0, "model_usage": {"claude-opus-4-8": {"inputTokens": 3097, "outputTokens": 2025, "cacheReadInputTokens": 142901, "cacheCreationInputTokens": 7834, "webSearchRequests": 0, "costUSD": 0.21590050000000002, "contextWindow": 1000000, "maxOutputTokens": 64000}}, "timed_out": false, "workspace": ""}
{"task": "pytest-dev__pytest-8399", "arm": "atelier", "rep": 1, "ok": true, "cost_usd": 0.1611985, "duration_ms": 47105, "duration_api_ms": 42182, "num_turns": 10, "input_tokens": 2836, "cache_read_tokens": 96787, "cache_creation_tokens": 6920, "output_tokens": 1177, "models": ["claude-opus-4-8"], "is_error": false, "result_excerpt": "All pass (59 passed, 9 skipped). Fix verified.", "valid": true, "validity_reason": "", "correct": true, "score": 1.0, "judge_model": "swebench", "judge_reason": "resolved", "saved_usd": 0.0, "saved_tokens": 0, "thinking_tokens": 0, "model_usage": {"claude-opus-4-8": {"inputTokens": 2836, "outputTokens": 1177, "cacheReadInputTokens": 96787, "cacheCreationInputTokens": 6920, "webSearchRequests": 0, "costUSD": 0.1611985, "contextWindow": 1000000, "maxOutputTokens": 64000}}, "timed_out": false, "workspace": ""}
{"task": "sympy__sympy-13877", "arm": "atelier", "rep": 1, "ok": true, "cost_usd": 0.8443109999999999, "duration_ms": 220882, "duration_api_ms": 203004, "num_turns": 26, "input_tokens": 3252, "cache_read_tokens": 605342, "cache_creation_tokens": 25063, "output_tokens": 10990, "models": ["claude-opus-4-8"], "is_error": false, "result_excerpt": "Fixed.\n\n**Root cause** \u2014 not the algorithm's domain. Bareiss fraction-free elimination is valid over any integral domain, including polynomial rings like \u2124[a], so symbolic entries are fine. The bug was pivot selection: `_eval_det_bareiss`'s inline `_find_pivot` used bare truthiness (`if val:`), so it accepted a *structurally* non-zero symbolic pivot that was actually zero. Dividing by that zero pivot (`/cumm`) produced `nan`, which later blew up in `factor_terms`' `< 0` comparison.\n\n**Fix** (`sympy/matrices/matrices.py`):\n- Replaced the `_find_pivot` workaround with `_find_reasonable_pivot(mat[:, 0], iszerofunc=iszerofunc)`, which actually tests for zero.\n- Added `iszerofunc=_is_zero_after_expand_mul` param + helper (`expand_mul(x) == 0`) \u2014 cheap, correct zero-test for the polynomial/rational entries Bareiss yields.\n- Imported `expand_mul`.\n\n**Result:** `f(5)=f(6)=f(7)=0` (correct \u2014 the `i+a*j` matrix is rank \u2264 2). Regression test added to `test_determinant`. Full matrix/determinant suites: 111 passed, no new failures (the 39 \"exceptions\" are pre-existing `collections.abc` deprecation noise, identical on baseline).", "valid": true, "validity_reason": "", "correct": true, "score": 1.0, "judge_model": "swebench", "judge_reason": "resolved", "saved_usd": 0.0, "saved_tokens": 0, "thinking_tokens": 0, "model_usage": {"claude-opus-4-8": {"inputTokens": 3252, "outputTokens": 10990, "cacheReadInputTokens": 605342, "cacheCreationInputTokens": 25063, "webSearchRequests": 0, "costUSD": 0.8443109999999999, "contextWindow": 1000000, "maxOutputTokens": 64000}}, "timed_out": false, "workspace": ""}
{"task": "sympy__sympy-13877", "arm": "atelier", "rep": 1, "ok": true, "cost_usd": 0.35589950000000004, "duration_ms": 89284, "duration_api_ms": 83884, "num_turns": 8, "input_tokens": 2961, "cache_read_tokens": 117089, "cache_creation_tokens": 15205, "output_tokens": 5220, "models": ["claude-opus-4-8"], "is_error": false, "result_excerpt": "Fixed. Full matrix test suite passes.\n\n**Your question:** No \u2014 Bareiss is *not* integer-only. It's a fraction-free elimination that's valid over any integral domain, including symbolic entries. The trouble here was the **pivot selection**, not the algorithm.\n\n**Root cause:** the inner `_find_pivot` in `_eval_det_bareiss` used plain truthiness (`if val:`) to pick a pivot. For a symbolic expression that is *structurally* nonzero but *mathematically* zero, that test picks it as the pivot, then `entry` divides by it \u2192 `nan`, which later hits `nan < 0` in `factor_terms` \u2192 `TypeError: Invalid NaN comparison`.\n\n**Fix** (`sympy/matrices/matrices.py`):\n- Replaced the `_find_pivot` workaround with `_find_reasonable_pivot`, passing a new `iszerofunc=_is_zero_after_expand_mul` (tests `expand_mul(x) == 0`, appropriate for polynomial/rational entries) so genuinely-zero pivots are rejected.\n- Added the `_is_zero_after_expand_mul` helper and imported `expand_mul`.\n\n`f(5)`/`f(6)`/`f(7)` now correctly return `0` (those matrices are rank-deficient) instead of `nan`/crashing.", "valid": true, "validity_reason": "", "correct": true, "score": 1.0, "judge_model": "swebench", "judge_reason": "resolved", "saved_usd": 0.0, "saved_tokens": 0, "thinking_tokens": 0, "model_usage": {"claude-opus-4-8": {"inputTokens": 2961, "outputTokens": 5220, "cacheReadInputTokens": 117089, "cacheCreationInputTokens": 15205, "webSearchRequests": 0, "costUSD": 0.35589950000000004, "contextWindow": 1000000, "maxOutputTokens": 64000}}, "timed_out": false, "workspace": ""}
